body:
We finally found the issue and made a fix for it.
The root cause was that `messenger` was not set inside this code block and we now have preference of using Waku2 instead of Waku: 

```golang
if b.statusNode != nil {
		wakuext := b.statusNode.WakuExtService()

		if wakuext != nil {
			messenger := wakuext.Messenger()

			if messenger != nil {
				if s == appStateForeground {
					messenger.ToForeground()
				} else {
					messenger.ToBackground()
				}
			}
		}

	}
```

https://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/b69042e7d7612d68996db9498cede8bb5d1599a8/api/geth_backend.go#L1305

and since messenger was not set none of the app state change logic was being executed,
This is fixed in : https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/3189
